Preheat your #grill{} to high. Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the pasta. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into 1cm wide long strips then chop widthways into roughly 1cm pieces. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} into rough chunks.

Put the aubergine on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with a little @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and toss to coat. Spread out evenly and pop under your grill until soft and browned, ~{15-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> TIP: Keep an eye on the aubergine - you may need to adjust the heat if it starts to brown too quickly!

Once cooked, remove from the grill but don't turn it off.

Meanwhile, add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} to your pan of boiling water and cook until 'al dente', about ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain the pasta in a #colander{} and return to the saucepan. Drizzle over a little @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

In the meantime, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and stir-fry until browned and crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the shallot, stir and cook until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and @chilli flakes{pinch} (only a pinch - they're hot!), stir together and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some).

Lower the heat to medium and simmer the sauce until it has thickened and reduced by half, ~{6-7%minutes}. Once the aubergine is cooked, stir it into the sauce. Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

Meanwhile, put the plum tomatoes and feta on the baking tray you used for the aubergine (no need to wash it). Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @ground black pepper{}. Gently combine them, then grill until the feta is browned and the tomatoes are soft, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir the pasta into the sauce and stir in half the parsley. Serve in #bowls{} with the grilled tomatoes and feta on top, sprinkled with the remaining parsley. Enjoy!